  "chapter": 3,
  "section": 5,
  "book": "geometry",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Key Concepts"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Parallel and Skew Lines:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "**Parallel lines:** Coplanar lines that do not intersect \n ($\\ell \\parallel m$)",
        "**Skew lines:** Non-coplanar lines that do not intersect",
        "**Transversal:** A line that intersects two or more coplanar \n lines at different points"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Angle Pairs Formed by a Transversal:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Corresponding angles",
        "Alternate interior angles",
        "Alternate exterior angles",
        "Same-side (consecutive) interior angles"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Parallel Line Theorems** (If $\\ell \\parallel m$):"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Corresponding angles are congruent",
        "Alternate interior angles are congruent",
        "Alternate exterior angles are congruent",
        "Same-side interior angles are supplementary"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Converses** (prove lines parallel):"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "If corresponding angles are congruent $\\Rightarrow$ parallel",
        "If alternate interior angles are congruent $\\Rightarrow$ parallel",
        "If same-side interior angles are supplementary $\\Rightarrow$ parallel"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Perpendicular Lines:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Lines that meet at right angles ($\\ell \\perp m$)",
        "If $t \\perp \\ell$ and $\\ell \\parallel m$, then $t \\perp m$",
        "If $\\ell \\perp t$ and $m \\perp t$, then $\\ell \\parallel m$"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "**Perpendicular Bisector:**"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        "Perpendicular to a segment at its midpoint",
        "Every point on it is equidistant from the segment's endpoints"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Review Exercises"
    }
  ]
}